# 🧠 Concept 1: Error Budgets

🔥 One of the most important concepts in Site Reliability Engineering (SRE).

---

## First Understand the Problem

Can a system ever be:

```text
100% available forever?
```

Practically:

❌ No

Failures happen.

Updates happen.

Hardware fails.

Networks fail.

---

## SRE Thinking

Instead of chasing 100% uptime:

Define an acceptable failure amount.

This is called:

👉 Error Budget

---

## Example

Suppose SLO:

```text
99.9% uptime
```

This means:

```text
0.1% downtime allowed
```

That allowed downtime is the error budget.

---

## Real-World Analogy

College attendance:

```text
Need 75%

Can miss 25%
```

That 25% is your attendance budget.

---

## Why Important?

Balances:

✔ Reliability

✔ Innovation

If error budget exhausted:

👉 Stop releasing risky changes.

---

## Interview Question

**Q: Why are error budgets useful?**

👉 They balance system reliability with development speed.

---

## Memory Trick

```text
SLO says target

Error budget says allowable failure
```

---

# 🧠 Concept 2: Stream Processing Systems

🔥 Very common in modern backend systems.

---

## Traditional Processing

Data stored first.

Processed later.

Example:

```text
Store logs

Analyze tomorrow
```

---

## Stream Processing

Process data continuously as it arrives.

---

## Examples

* Stock prices
* GPS tracking
* Fraud detection
* Emergency alerts

---

## Real-World Analogy

Water flowing through a river.

You analyze water continuously,

not after collecting entire river.

---

## Why Useful?

✔ Real-time insights

✔ Low latency

✔ Immediate reactions

---

## Examples

* Apache Kafka
* Apache Flink

---

## Interview Question

**Q: Difference between batch processing and stream processing?**

👉 Batch processes stored data later, while stream processing handles data continuously in real time.

---

## Memory Trick

```text
Batch = Later

Stream = Now
```

---

# ⚙️ Concept 3: Unified Memory Architecture (UMA)

🔥 Important modern hardware concept.

---

## Traditional System

CPU memory and GPU memory are separate.

```text
CPU RAM

↓

Copy Data

↓

GPU Memory
```

Extra overhead.

---

## UMA Solution

CPU and GPU share memory.

---

## Real-World Analogy

Two people using same notebook instead of copying pages back and forth.

---

## Benefits

✔ Less data copying

✔ Lower latency

✔ Simpler programming

---

## Why Important?

Very useful in:

* AI workloads
* Graphics
* Mobile devices

---

## Interview Question

**Q: Why is unified memory useful?**

👉 Because CPU and GPU can access the same data without expensive copying.

---

## Memory Trick

```text
One memory

Many processors
```

---

# ⚙️ Concept 4: Multi-Agent AI Systems

🔥 One of the hottest AI topics today.

---

## Single Agent

One AI handles everything.

Problem:

❌ Limited specialization

---

## Multi-Agent System

Many AI agents collaborate.

---

## Example

Travel Planning

### Agent 1

Search flights

---

### Agent 2

Search hotels

---

### Agent 3

Create itinerary

---

## Real-World Analogy

Company departments.

Each team specializes.

Together they solve larger problems.

---

## Advantages

✔ Scalability

✔ Specialization

✔ Better problem solving

---

## Challenge

Agents must coordinate correctly.

---

## Interview Question

**Q: Why use multiple AI agents?**

👉 Different agents can specialize in different tasks and collaborate on complex workflows.

---

## Memory Trick

```text
One problem

Many specialized agents
```

---

